; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The evidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">shows that economic growth and demand for transport go hand in hand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ransport infrastructure allows businesses to grow, work together and access a wide range of customers, suppliers and skilled labour. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">create opportunities for regeneration</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, and mak</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a more attractive place to invest. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It can help to re-balance the economy, rather than accentuate existing divisions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">apacity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">hallenge</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Transport demand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rown hand in hand with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">conomic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">opulation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> growth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eal GDP is expected to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">increase by 56% over the next 20 years</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> population is projected to grow by 11 million people between 2010 and 2035. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This will put our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">busy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">networks under</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> pressure. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Government is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">responding by i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nvesting heavily in transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We will invest</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> £73bn </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in transport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> between 2015/16 and 2020/21. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This includes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">trebling of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">spending on major road schemes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by 2021</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Network Rail will spend over £35bn fro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m 2014-19, allowing it to continue a substantial programme of expansion and renewal.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">But in spite of this investment, we expect our transport network to remain under pressure. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Our forecasts predict that by 2040 traffic on strategic roads will grow by 46%. Under certain projected scenarios, traffic could grow by as much as 72%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">On the rai</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lway,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> number of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">passenger journeys</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has increased by 54% over the last decade to 1.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, an annual year on year growth rate of 4.4%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Intercity journeys increased by 65% over the same period</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> – an annual growth rate of 5.2%.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">growth </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">taken place</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> alongside advances in mobile technology.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The rail freight sector as also shown strong growth.  Freight carried by rail has increased by an average of 2.5% annually in the last 20 years.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We are tackling </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">commuter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">capacity through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Crossrail</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Thameslink</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">upgrade</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the Northern Hub</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Midland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and East Coast Main Lines </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will benefit from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">electrification and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Intercity Express Programme (IEP). However, the West Coast Main Line, the busiest mixed use railway in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Europe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is under particular press</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with no easy fixes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  It has seen trip growth of 36% between 2006 and 2009. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Despite a major £9bn upgrade lasting a decade, it</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is now close to its planned capacity in terms of the number of trains</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> at peak times</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Already </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reliability is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">suffering</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">On</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a typical weekday </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Euston, over 40% of trains in the morning and evening peak periods already have passengers standing. More than 10% of passengers arriving on peak hour services into </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Birmingham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, Leeds, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Manchester</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Sheffield</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> are standing.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Capacity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">constraints are being felt now and the pressure is set to grow over</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> time.  We need to take action; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and rail schemes have long lead times.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">onnectivity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> opportunity</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Developing a solution to this challenge presents an opportunity not only to create bett</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">er travel conditions, but also to improve connectivity – with shorter more reliable journey times – particularly between our major cities. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Improved connectivity, through reduced journey times, can help deliver additional benefits and more economic growth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> than comes from extra capacity alone. It can help re-balance the economy by stimulating and strengthening regional economies and help to make </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Britain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more attractive in the global marketplace</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Question 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">:  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Why </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">HS2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Government’s role is to build a stronger, more balanced economy capable of delivering lasting growth and widely shared prosperity. Transport plays a key part in this. In that context, our objectives are: </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to provide sufficient capacity to meet long term de</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">mand, and to improve resilience </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nd reliability across the network; and</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to improve connectivity by delivering better journey times and making travel easier.</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Any solution must</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> also</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> minimise disruption to the existing network;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> us</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> proven technology;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be affor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dable and good value to the taxpayer; and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">minimise impacts on local communities and the environment.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We have considered a full range of options.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Doing nothing or</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ricing people off the railway </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> not realistic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">solutions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">omestic aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> not a sustainable way to address the challenge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ur roads are also under pressure and we do not believe that increasing road capacity alone is the solution. Motorways cannot match the speed of high speed rail, and it is difficult to increase the capacity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of urban roads. </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ail investment is the best way to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">meet the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">capacity challenges we face. In the past we have carried out incremental improvements to the existing network. The decision to be made now is whether to build a new north-south railway as well.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e have carried out extensive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">analysis</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> incremental improvements to the existing network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, and they</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ould</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> not achieve our</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> objectives. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">While they may have positive benefit to cost ratios, t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hey </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">not provide </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the step change in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">capacity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> needed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to meet the long</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> term demand on the north-south railways</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Nor can they offer anything like the reductions in journey times that HS2 can, and they would likely </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">exace</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rbate the problems with service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> performance. </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The best </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rail upgrade alternative to HS2 would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> only offer a 36% increase in peak hour capacity at Euston,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> cost £20bn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> deliver less than half the overall benefits, and result in 14 years of weekend closures. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The only</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> option</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that meets our objectives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is a new north-south railway. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">While</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a new hig</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h speed line</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will cost</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 9% </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">more than a conventional line, this is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">more than outweighed by the economic benefits from radically reducing journey times between our main cities. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In terms of the future well-being of the country as a whole, a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> high speed line </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the best choice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Question 3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">:  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What are the benefits of HS2?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Capacity</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">HS2 provides a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">step change in capacity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">could </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">triple</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the number of seats departing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Euston in the peak hour</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and double the number of trains per hour.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">HS2 will benefit passengers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">across the network. Transferring intercity services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> onto HS2, will release </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">capacity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on the existing network to introduce new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">commuter and regional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will also improve service reliability and resilience</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Network Rail estimates that over 100 cities and towns could benefit from new or improved services as a result of capacity released on the existing network.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We intend to make the most of this additional capacity in order to maximise the benefits from the n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ew railway whilst ensuring value for money for tax-payers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">One of the key aims for future service patterns is that all towns or cities which currently have a direct service to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will retain broadly comparable or better services once HS2 is completed. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Connectivity benefits</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">HS2 will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">drastically reduce journey times. C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">entral London to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Birmingham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will take</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">49 minutes rather than 1 hour 24 minutes today and from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Mancheste</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in 1 hour 8 minutes rather than the 2 hours 8 minutes it takes today. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he economic geography of the country will be transformed with many more people being brought to within one hour of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. However, HS2 is about more than transport to and from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Some of the biggest reductions in journeys will be between regional cities, such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Birmingham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Leeds</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 7.7pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">HS2 will connect eight out of our 10 largest cities: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size: